### **âœ… 1\. What is Quartile Deviation?**

### **ğŸ”¹ Connection with Median**

* **Quartile Deviation (Q.D.)** measures **spread of the middle 50%** of the data.

* It is also called the **Semi-Interquartile Range**.

![][image1]

* While **Median (Qâ‚‚)** splits data into **2 equal halves**,  
   **Qâ‚** and **Qâ‚ƒ** further split it into **4 quarters**:

| Quartile | Meaning |
| ----- | ----- |
| Qâ‚ | Lower quartile (25%) |
| Qâ‚‚ | Median (50%) |
| Qâ‚ƒ | Upper quartile (75%) |
